Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}. Thinly slice @celery{2.5%oz}. Strip
@thyme{¼%oz} leaves from stems; mince leaves until you have 1 tsp. Dice
@demi-baguette{1} into ½-inch pieces.

> 4 SERVINGS: Mince thyme leaves until you have 2 tsp.

In a #small bowl{}, combine half the @chicken stock concentrate{1}
(you'll use the rest later) and @water{¼%cup}.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use ½ cup water.

Pat @pork tenderloin{12%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{4%tsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add pork and sear, turning occasionally, until browned on all sides,
~{4-8%minutes}. Remove pan from heat.

Transfer pork to one side of a #baking sheet{}.

Toss @green beans{6%oz} on opposite side of baking sheet from pork with a
drizzle of olive oil, salt, and pepper.

Roast on middle rack until pork is cooked through and green beans are browned
and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}. Remove from oven and let pork rest at least
~{5%minutes}.

Heat @butter{3%tbsp} and a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add baguette; toast, stirring occasionally, until golden
brown and crisp, ~{5-7%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe
out pan.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add celery and
shallot; cook until tender, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Add
minced thyme and baguette. Stir in stock mixture until absorbed, ~{1-2%minutes}.
Turn off heat; cover to keep warm.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 3 TBSP butter.

> TIP: Prefer a softer stuffing? Add a splash more water after stirring in
> stock mixture.

While pork rests, heat pan used to sear pork over medium-high heat. Add
@fig jam{2%tbsp}, @water{¼%cup}, and remaining @chicken stock concentrate{1}
Bring to a boil and cook, stirring occasionally, until reduced,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with salt and
pepper.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 1/3 cup water and 2 TBSP butter.

Thinly slice pork crosswise.

Divide pork, green beans, and stuffing between plates. Spoon pan sauce over
pork and serve.